column1: 11026;instagram;2019-02-24 12:35:48;FALSE;"today we went and caught a couple of fringe shows
column2: which was my first time out and about since getting some sad news.

column1: an intervention order has been filed that potentially gags me from talking publicly about some or all of my experiences with trauma.
it comes into effect shortly so i’m posting this now before i’m unable to explain the change of pace.
this blatantly abuses a system designed to keep people safe and i find it repulsive.
it’s an attempt to regain control of a victim and continue psychologically abusing them by taking away their voice and agency.
but. i am choosing to see the opportunities here.

column2: this finally proved that abuse victims are not supported
column5: which is a resolve i didn’t have clear evidence of.

column1: it also encourages me to write privately — where i can edit
column2: where i can probe and research
column3: where i can produce work worth publishing.

column2: it informed me that perpetrators dislike being exposed
column3: meaning a victim can hold great power when they speak out.

column1: so this is actually a bundle of gifts:
the gift of resolution from having proof the system fails.
the gift of motivation to become a writer.
the gift of feeling my power and agency again.
i hope that explains to loved ones why i might take a step back from being as vocal.
but when someone helps you in ways no one else could there is really only one thing to say:

column1: in a box i‘ve discovered my old nameless doll. a gray layer of dust covers her close-cropped brown hair. when i was nine
column2: one of myabusers had forced me to cut my own beautiful long hair short. i‘d hated my short
column4: dark curls; and in my anger
column5: i‘d cut off my baby doll‘s hair
column6: so her beauty could bite the dust along with mine. now we‘re equal.

column1: now i undress my doll and hold her under the faucet. carefully
column2: i clean her with soap and a sponge
column3: washing the dust out of her eyes. i dry her body with a towel
column4: then for a long time i hold her
column6: to my heart. her presence seems to ease my pain
column7: to comfort me. “now that you‘re bathed and clean
column8: i‘ll paint a picture of you to give you back your dignity

column3: healing and relief drive away my rage. the water reaches up to the doll’s nose. she can breathe
column4: but cannot move or talk. if she does
column5: she‘ll drown. it‘s precisely how i felt as a child.

column1: 11141;instagram;2019-02-24 11:00:17;FALSE;"🏆第91回 #アカデミー賞 全部門受賞予想🏆
#metoo #timesup 運動の活発化する中行われた昨年の第90回アカデミー賞では、
【作品賞受賞有力作が全て女性が主人公】
【史上6人目の監督賞ノミニーが誕生】
【#lgbt を描いた作品が外国語映画賞受賞】などとハリウッドの“空気”が顕著に反映されたアカデミー賞となった。
今年もその系譜は受け継がれているようだ。
※今年の作品賞の主人公のキャラクターの一覧を載せてみます。（あえて直接的な表現を使いますので注意を）
『#ブラッククランズマン』→黒人
『#ボヘミアンラプソディ』→移民
『#女王陛下のお気に入り』→主要キャスト全員女性
『#roma ローマ』→メキシコ人女性
『#アリースター誕生』→片方女性
『#バイス』→主要キャスト全員オスカーノミネート経験者
女性重視の風潮、かつてのホワイトオスカー問題からの必ず黒人俳優入れる流れなど、良くも悪くもハリウッドの“風潮”にしっかりと寄せてきた結果となっている。唯一“寄せてない”バイスもアカデミー賞のモロ好みな俳優ばかり揃えているため、ある意味順当とも言える。
さて、シンプルな予想に移ろう。
bffca、英アカデミー賞と特に重要な前哨戦で作品賞を獲得した『#ローマ』が大本命だが、果たして信じ切っていいのか。
外国語、モノクロ、去年まで冷遇されていたネトフリ配給、キャストほぼ無名、gg賞やサテライト賞での候補落ちなど意外とマイナス面は多い。
何より英アカデミー賞と米アカデミー賞の作品賞は4年連続で異なっている。最近では、その時点で作品賞最有力と言われた #ララランド や #スリービルボード を退けてまで、だ。
個人的には『女王陛下のお気に入り』がクサイと思っている。早くからアカデミー賞の本命と称された今作、脚本賞や編集賞候補にも上がり、当落線上にいた監督賞でも逆転ノミネートを果たし、一度落ちた勢いが復活してきてる印象を受ける。
そして『グリーンブック』。gg賞にpgaを受賞するなど、実はローマ以上に前哨戦で評価されてるとも言える。監督らの不適切なスキャンダルが頻出したり、米レビューサイトでは評価が真っ二つという状況なのも気がかりだが、こちらを本命としている媒体も多いんじゃないだろうか。
毎年のように反トランプ色を出すオスカー、今年はそこが最重要テーマなんじゃないかと見ている。何せこの作品、アメリカメキシコ合作映画である。何かとメキシコを敵に回すトランプへの対抗のメッセージとして、アメリカとメキシコの繋がりを強調する結果にさせるんじゃないかと。その思惑を抜きにしても、ローマの作品賞予想は変えるつもりは無い。
何よりアカデミー賞が好みな“芸術性”と“多様性”を兼ね備え、主人公も外国人女性で監督賞受賞最有力というのも心強い。
そして、今年の俳優部門は全てが混戦模様。
その中でも最も予想が難しかった主演女優賞は前哨戦もスピーチの好感度の面でも一歩抜けた感のあるクローズ、一波乱ありそうな助演女優賞はなんだかんだで前評判通りキングで決まりそう。
助演男優賞は2年ぶりに2度目のオスカーを手にしそうなアリ。主演男優賞は願望も含め、フレディマーキュリーを現代に蘇らせ、重要前哨戦も全て抑えたマレックと予想。
その他、外国語映画賞の受賞は間違いないと言われる『ローマ』。しかし監督賞にサプライズノミネートを果たしたほど人気があるポーランドの『cold war』も少し匂う。こちらが受賞したとしたら『ローマ』は作品賞間違いなしという流れになるが...。
長編ドキュメンタリー賞は女性として米国史上2人目の最高判事となったルース・ギンズバーグを追った内容というだけでココが受賞すると確信。去年からハリウッドを支配するのは“女性の素晴らしさを讃えようという流れ”。前哨戦とか関係無しにココなんじゃないかと思う。歌曲賞ノミネートも大きい。
同じくほとんど前情報の無い短編アニメーション賞も、ピクサー初の女性監督作『bao』かなと思ったが、この部門はアニー賞の結果と被るため、候補の中で唯一アニー賞にもノミネートされ受賞も果たした『weekends』で決まりと見る。
長編アニメーション賞は前哨戦を圧倒する『#スパイダーマン』と予想も、基本はディズニーやピクサーの独壇場である部門。正直『#インクレディブルファミリー』のサプライズもあり得そうな気がする。
そして日本からの『#万引き家族』『#未来のミライ』はどちらもノーチャンスだろう。前者はローマに作品賞の票が流れた時、後者は受賞の可能性があるスパイダーマン、インクレディブル、#犬ヶ島 で票が割れた時、ワンチャンある。
今年は本当に難しい。作品賞候補作の中で最も受賞が無さそうな1本さえ絞りきれない。ボヘミアンが来ようがブラックパンサーが来ようがサプライズではない横一線状態。最後の最後に抜け出し、笑う作品はどれか？
第91回アカデミー賞は明日8:30から！皆さん年に1度の映画の祭典を楽しみましょう😊

column1: 11161;instagram;2019-02-24 10:30:43;FALSE;"in the spirit of my last post
column2: and continuously trying to understand each other
column3: i wanted to share a really cool conversation i had with a friend regarding my previous post about the ill-advised #metoo joke from a stranger on a dating app. one of my good guy friends saw it and genuinely wanted to understand why i handled it the way i did. why i even let the guy play it off as a joke
column4: at first. and i had to think about it
column5: and talk it out to really understand why
column6: myself. i didn't pause to run it by any of my friends first. i just went with my gut reaction and trusted the weird feeling i got. which is a state of assertiveness that it can often take us longer than guys to achieve. i'm 32 and have only had a handle on it for a few years.

column1: this response in particular came from a few places. partly it was the class my momma gave me
column2: to state my truth without feeling the need to ""argue my side"". (it doesn't always beat my inclination for debate
column3: but usually wins in serious situations.) partly it was our conditioning as females to protect the egos of men
column4: out of a misplaced sense of status and accomodation for a potentially harmful escalation. and partly it was growing up with the amazing examples of people like @amypoehlersmartgirls
column6: specifically through the art of comedy - the context i'm apt to learn in - who openly expose the idea of *everyone* placing self-respect far above the ego of *anyone* else
column7: no matter who they are. making that the default

column1: so thank you to all the confident
column2: badass women in my real life (i'm lucky to have many)
column3: and in the public eye for setting great examples and taking on such a big discussion. i will try to do the same. and thank you to all the badass guys out there
column4: really trying to understand the other side. i think it's gonna work. we just have to keep doing it.✌🤟✊";;en;#MeToo

column2: time for the big question: tell us one life-changing travel incident/ moment that you still cherish or that has changed you/ your outlook as a person.

column1: my first trip as a serious traveller was to spiti with wonderful world. spiti was remote
column2: with stark landscapes that i found interesting and engrossing. the road-journeys were arduous – but drivers would always make way and help travellers would help each other out (give driving instructions
column3: move rocks away to clear out roads). this camaraderie and the peace that i found in the quietness of ancient monasteries was incomparable. as i smiled with monks
column4: explored painted scenes from the bodhisattva’s life on crumbling monastery walls
column5: a shift happened in my soul. this feeling was accentuated while having simple home-cooked meals and sipping the potent local-brew with spitian families crowding around their warm hearths. the women sang mountain melodies and we danced together with abandon.

column2: i felt that i had touched the beauty of living that eludes us as we rush through our busy days in cities. it made me understand what it meant to be fully present in a moment – a sense of completeness and of abundance.""
according to you why should women travel?

column1: our world today is in massive constant flux. political and social dilemmas dominate public discourses while humanity as a whole stands on the brink of ecological disaster.

column2: i believe we live in a better world now - a post #metoo world where we can openly debate issues such as gender parity
column3: discrimination and bias. i believe that as women
column4: we have more options to travel now – solo
column5: with like-minded people or with friends & family. it is up to us to have these experiences and broaden how we see the world."" ~ @suds.muse #womenofwonderfulworld #womenontheirowntrip #wonderfulworld";;en;#metoo

column1: being in jail for fighting back against domestic violence is wrong.  domestic violence is wrong. yelling
column5: punching walls or psychologically manipulating & abusing anyone is wrong.  we all have rough days
column6: but there is a difference between lashing out at loved ones when life scares us and constantly whipping them into unrecognizable pain sponges. please help educate and end this cycle.  the more we can feel comfortable sharing our painful stories
column7: the more victems can step forward and find a voice that was robbed from them.

column1: my friend @nara_walker helped console me in iceland when i suffered a miscarriage while recovering from extreme domestic abuse. i was a missing person for 5 days
column2: tied in an isolated pine forest in south west australia 16 weeks pregnant. so i fled to 'travel' or 'run forward' like i'm known to do
column4: flaky 'safety plan' after safety plan.  she was going through her own hell after recently being publicly assaulted by her husband who forced himself on her.  when he forced his tongue in her mouth
column5: her jaw reacted in fear and bit it off.  so she got arrested
column6: and has been living the past year in fear
column8: unable to leave.  now she is in jail. where is the justice.  why is this ok?  why do so many people ignore this basic wrong?  i asked myself many times why no one helped me
column9: why no one stopped him.  why i spent my childhood protecting my crying mum at the foot of my bed.  not my business is usually what they say.  well one day it's your daughter or wife or grandmother.  it's your business. #bringnarahome #endthecycle #domesticviolence #instadomesticviolence  #domesticviolenceawareness #emotionalabuse #domesticabuse #narcissisticabuse #mentalhealth #sociopath #narcissist #metoo  #gaslighting #domesticviolencesurvivor #mentalhealthawareness #ptsd #sexualabuse #survivor #psychologicalabuse #selfcare #verbalabuse #abusesurvivor #trauma #toxicrelationships  #stopdomesticviolence";;en;#bringnarahome

11374;instagram;2019-02-24 04:09:21;FALSE;"i may be able to shut people out.
but i do suffer in silence.
thats the reason i can easily shut people out:
the silence of the night keeps my thoughts running.
about every little lesson of life that i didn’t pick up straight away.
about enduring cycles of suffering that i kept trying to break.
but no matter how many times i will fall down.
no matter how tired i get of trying.
i will always dust myself off and try again.
and i wont point fingers either 🙏🏽 #kehmet #queens #royals

11383;instagram;2019-02-24 04:23:49;FALSE;"today was one of the days nobody wants to talk about. the days that almost break you and make you want to cry in your car. i have definitely been all up in my feels and borderline a brat today. if you saw in my stories i went with my sister in-law her boyfriend and my husband to an escape room. hudson is usually super chill so i brought him too but of course he decided he hated the tula and then preceded to throw up on himself and i poor dude. yes it may seem stupid that i was sad that i had to sit in the car while everyone got to finish the game but no one else there knew what it is like being a mom and making these sacrifices. they don’t know what it’s like to have to stop what you’re doing and nurse your child
column2: get up with them during all hours of the night
column3: or just having them depend on you for every little thing. i love hudson to death and would walk the ends of the earth for him but that doesn’t mean it’s always easy. for the mama needing to hear this today it’s okay to be upset and it doesn’t make you a bad mom because you feel like you are missing out💕.

column1: #motherhoodintheraw #motherhoodrising #allupinmyfeels #inmyfeelings #momlifeisthebestlife #badmom #hardday #emotionsmatter #mentalhealth #momminainteasy #youngliving #younglivingessentialoils #mamabear #mompreneur #momboss #momblogger #momlife #momlifeisthebestlife #motherhustler #metoo #oilymama #crunchymom #cleanliving #knowbetterdobetter  #toxicfreehome #wellnessjourney #wellnesswarrior #mountainmama";"today was one of the days nobody wants to talk about. the days that almost break you and make you want to cry in your car. i have definitely been all up in my feels and borderline a brat today. if you saw in my stories i went with my sister in-law her boyfriend and my husband to an escape room. hudson is usually super chill so i brought him too but of course he decided he hated the tula and then preceded to throw up on himself and i poor dude. yes it may seem stupid that i was sad that i had to sit in the car while everyone got to finish the game but no one else there knew what it is like being a mom and making these sacrifices. they don’t know what it’s like to have to stop what you’re doing and nurse your child

column1: 11391;instagram;2019-02-24 04:30:47;FALSE;"r. kelly was charged with 10 counts of criminal sexual abuse involving at least three underage victims in a chicago court friday following decades of rumors and allegations that the r&b star was abusing women and underage girls.

column2: a spokeswoman for the cook county state's attorney's office
column3: announced in a press conference that charges had been filed against the 52-year-old grammy winner. the 52-year-old singer
column4: whose real name is robert kelly
column5: arrived at a chicago precinct in a van about 8:15 p.m. friday. he was arrested and is expected to be held overnight and appear saturday in bond court.

column1: kelly has denied allegations of sexual misconduct involving women and underage girls for decades.
r. kelly is one of the top-selling recording artists of all time. he has won multiple grammys
column2: including for his hit song ""i believe i can fly."" his arrest sets the stage for another #metoo-era celebrity trial after bill cosby went to prison last year.

column1: 11456;instagram;2019-02-24 02:34:03;FALSE;"today i went off on a man standing in line behind me for repeatedly touching my lower back and butt while waiting in line for the register. his response when i asked him to back up and to stop touching me was ""well there's nowhere else to stand"" (he had at least two feet of space between him and the man behind him and less than a foot of space between me and him). if you know me
column2: you know that i did not take his response kindly.
if something like this happens to you or if a stranger ever makes you feel personally uncomfortable
column3: stand up for yourself. call them out. make a scene. raise your voice and let everyone around you know what that person is trying to do to you. don't just take it. don't awkwardly try to shimmy away and hope they stop
column4: because they won't. it does not matter who you are or who they are
column5: what state you're in or what you're wearing. make a spectacle out of them. and if you see another woman in an uncomfortable situation like this
column6: stand up for them. don't just sit there and watch.

column1: and since the last time something (somewhat) similar like this happened to me and i had ""friends"" tell me
column2: ""oh well i mean look at what you were wearing""
column3: this is what i looked like. dirty and smelling of dog and horse after a full day of work.

column1: it does not matter what you look like or what you are doing
column2: you do not deserve to be touched by a stranger without your permission. to all my ladies

column1: 11581;instagram;2019-02-23 00:47:14;FALSE;"having the courage to share your story is an important part of the healing process throughout separation or divorce.
sharing with people who are kind
column2: empathetic and compassionate is absolutely essential
column3: allowing you to release the internal burdens amplified by the power of your mind.
there comes a responsibility to own your story. which is why it’s so important
column5: to bring your full awareness to the present moment
column6: knowing that ‘your story’ is just that—a past event told through the lens of your eyes only (an event that we have added our own meaning and emotion to). your ex will have have witnessed the exact same event through a completely different lens and vantage point. neither is right or wrong.

column1: 昨日日記に残した、洗面台の鏡について
会社のトイレの鏡では歯磨きやメイクを直す、服を脱ぐ事は当然ないが
家の洗面台は脱衣所であり服を脱ぐ、ある時はt字カミソリが置いていた。
娘はお年頃なのでそこでムダ毛処理とかもしていたのだろう。
それを一般人の中村や近所の住人が見ると言うことはどうなんだろう。
私が思うヤンマーが関係しているなら、会社で謳っている「倫理」「モラル」と矛盾してないか？
それよりも盗撮という犯罪。
そこまでする何かがあったのか？
ただ何かの私の不利な証拠を作りたかっただけでは？
むこのそう近畿住研という管理会社を利用して。

column1: #rkelly’s hopes of doing a tour of europe in april have been all but dashed now that he is facing new criminal charges.

kelly defiantly scheduled concerts in two locations in #germany and one in the #netherlands in april despite a cloud of legal issues in the wake of the recently aired lifetime documentary series “#survivingrkelly” that delved into his alleged history of sexually abusing young women and girls. kelly has denied engaging in sexual misconduct.
but the concerts appear to be scuttled with friday’s charges accusing him of sexual abuse involving four victims.

column2: venues and promoters abroad were feeling heat to cancel future concerts by the r&b star.

column3: said activists knew of kelly’s planned european performances and were tipped off to his attempts to get picked up by promoters in latin american countries.

column2: maad’m muscle went quiet for a while. for those of you that don’t know

column4: i had my “biggest supporter” telling me i was doing everything wrong
column7: no one will buy my products. i made a choice to remove myself from this environment and fought for my happiness and success. i am now back full force and ready to help you reach your goals. there will be some major changes being made to maad’m muscle so stay tuned ladies. the best is yet to come 💜

column1: hello ladies. i want to reintroduce myself to you. my name is amanda and i am the owner of maad’m muscle. as you may have noticed
column2: maad’m muscle went quiet for a while. for those of you that don’t know
column3: i started this company while i was pregnant and in a very toxic relationship. i put my heart into formulating amazing products to help women reach their fitness goals and turned my dream into a reality. unfortunately i let the overwhelming stress and negativity in my life prevent me from investing what i should have into this company. i allowed a toxic person to change my opinion of myself and i started to doubt my ability to grow my business. no matter how much i tried to believe in my products and myself
column4: i had my “biggest supporter” telling me i was doing everything wrong
column7: no one will buy my products. i made a choice to remove myself from this environment and fought for my happiness and success. i am now back full force and ready to help you reach your goals. there will be some major changes being made to maad’m muscle so stay tuned ladies. the best is yet to come 💜

column1: 11639;instagram;2019-02-23 22:42:35;FALSE;"as a woman who has been a victim of sexual harassment and attempted assault and knowing so many friends and family members who have as well
column2: words cannot express the impact this shoot had on me. thank you @mcluap for letting me help you and the rest of the @therealdeal tell this important story. and most importantly thank you stella lee

column2: then you do it the same way the next time
column3: but the next time it won’t be correct. the only time you feel like you can kind of breathe—and i say “kind of” because you know it’s temporary—is when they are gone. .

column1: after i had just had my baby
column2: i hurt my knee and needed to be on crutches. i also had a one and two-year-old to take care of. but my husband wanted to go out of town and i was completely ok with that. i would have rather been hobbling around with three little ones than have him around to add to my stress. how abnormal is that? but the thing is
column3: this is our “normal” so we don’t even question it. we go with the flow. .

column2: pjs and blankets. my husband had been making moves to try to have sex
column3: so he told me to just wipe him down with a warm towel and let them go back to sleep. he legitimately got pissed at me for staying up with my son. and a couple of times when i dozed off when my son did
column4: he came in and woke me up. again
column5: not normal. but life with these people are anything but. •

column2: you decided to make traveling and exploring our world your mission. whether you are a beginner or an experienced traveler
column3: we all know it isn't easy. sometimes it's scary to travel to another country alone
column5: to not know the language and be completely lost. .

column1: the story behind spiritual nomad started long before i could remember but on my first solo trip to switzerland in 2014 solidified my idea. i moved to switzerland to live and work. i had a difficult time integrating into a new culture
column2: trying to fit in with the group of people i haven’t seen in over six years and being so far away from home. i felt like because i was traveling the world and staying in beautiful places i couldn’t complain. no one seemed to understand especially my friends and family back home. after a few months of trying to make it work
column3: i decided to head off to italy to try again. .

column1: nothing would ever prepare me for what i experienced in pisa. i was sexually assaulted by a hostel owner. that was the straw that broke the camel’s back. i felt alone
column2: defeated and homesick. i felt like a failure that i was “quitting” my dream of traveling the world to go home.
i wish i had reached out to someone to comfort me. i wanted a friendly face
column3: someone i could talk to without judgment or explanation and be accepted with love. i came up with the idea to make t-shirts for spiritual nomad. .

column1: let me explain. the idea is for you to buy two shirts; one for yourself and the other to give to a friend; now you know you’re not alone. if you ever see anyone with a spiritual nomad shirt or product
column2: you’ll know you both are on the same page
column3: like an friendly ally you can reach out to without judgment or explanation. .

column1: a spiritual nomad is a life choice and it may not necessarily mean traveling for you. it's any journey you are on. a nomad by definition is a person who does not stay long in the same place. traveler or not
column2: as people we are constantly evolving. everything around is always changing whether you want to be aware of it or not. column6: incest and addictions to a place of healing.

column1: with an emphasis on helping others heal from their past
column2: the overall theme of sabella’s book is about being a victorious survivor rather than living life as a victim. sabella discusses how to use one’s spirituality as an asset and a tool in the recovery process; the author reveals how she herself felt a connection to “the divine” that helped her find the way through difficult times in her life and bring it into focus. throughout the book
column3: sabella also shares the reiki energy
column4: spiritual connections and positive affirmations that supported her and made it possible for her to turn her pain into joy. “one in five girls and one in twenty boys in this country alone have experienced sexual abuse
column5: incest or other forms of abuse or assault

emmy hurley claimed she had a terrifying experience in tampa

she hopped in the ride-share and had no idea anything was amiss as they drove off. it wasn’t until she received a phone call from her actual uber driver that she realized the mistake she had made. “last night i was picked up by an uber. same car
column2: female driver. i made a mistake
column3: ” the facebook post read. “i got in before checking
column4: as she opened the back door for me from her seat.” she said the woman she thought was her uber driver drove around erratically for 10 minutes and didn’t speak to her when she got in the car. about 10 minutes in
column5: my actual uber called me asking where i was
column7: because in that instant i knew. ‘a car … i think i need help’.” hurley then claimed her real uber driver
column9: told her to stay on the phone and get out of the car immediately.

column2: she claimed that when she asked the driver to stop she “refused” and ignored her request. “i told her she was driving by my friends (random girls i saw) and they would call the cops
column3: ” hurley said in the post. “she slowed a little
column4: pointing at her phone saying ‘uber. i take you back then’.” she told her she wanted to be dropped off where they were and made the decision to jump out of the moving car when the driver didn’t comply. tampa police announced on wednesday that the incident was reported to them and they discovered that it was nothing more than a misunderstanding

column1: 11903;instagram;2019-02-23 16:10:49;FALSE;"""pulling out"" or the ""withdrawal method"" is a practice that has been around long before we even came up with a word for it. it refers to the act (with no condom on) a man withdraws from a woman just as he's about to ejaculate
column2: in order to prevent pregnancy. it is an unreliable method of preventing pregnancy because it may or may not work and leave you vulnerable to the consequences. first of all
column3: it doesn't protect against hiv/aids.  it's possible to get a host of other infections such as chlamydia/hpv by not using a condom. neither does it account for pre-ejaculation. meaning that you are possibly risking pregnancy way before you’re even close to finshing. also
column4: it is possible to ""pull out"" too late or ejaculate a little bit before pulling out. even if semen gets on the outer genitals (vulva)
column5: pregnancy may be possible. the ""withdrawal method"" tends to be less effective than other forms of contraception. with a pill
column7: you are guaranteed more protection against pregnancy
column8: hiv/aids and std/stis. (not 100% but that’s a story for another day).

column2: do the terms hidden vaults and ghost apps mean anything to you? no? well
column3: they should. these apps can be on your child's phone and at first glance
column5: if you open them up you will likely find inappropriate photos
column6: videos and messages from their peers as well as strangers. these secret vaults or repositories allow your child to hide inappropriate and even pornographic content without you or anyone else being any the wiser. so what can you do to identify these apps? first
column7: check your child's phone to see if they have multiple apps with the same functionality such as a calculator or a camera. if so
column8: check the content of both. an immediate red flag is a ""simple"" app such as a calculator or camera requiring a password. next
column9: go to the settings in your child's phone and check for apps that are taking up an immense amount of storage space. a calculator or camera shouldn't be anywhere close to the top of the list. lastly
column10: consider using parental controls to prevent them from downloading apps
column12: on their devices without your permission. understanding the technology that your child has access to is a major step in preventing them from becoming prey for a predator
